name: Air Terjun Umejero
address: P25Q+M89, Umejero, Busung Biu, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81154, Indonesia
review 1: Total of 15-20min walk from the main road. Fairly steep walkable concrete path all the way to the bottom. Doable by motorbike but if it rains it is quite slippery. When at the bottom (where there is a bridge crossing the river), an overgrown walkable trail goes up the river to the waterfall. It's remote so you won't find any tourists.
review 2: It is closed and the trail is growing in. Level 6 out if ten for motor bike riding skill level. Small trail with mossy cement. Be careful or walk down the hill. I would be pretty certain any adventurer that goes here will get the peacefulness of being alone. It is deep enough to swim here also which is a huge plus.
review 4: Very nice, peaceful waterfall. Not the easiest road to use if your not fully confident on your bike, don't go.
review 5: A real gem of this area. Extremely not touristy you will likely be the only one there. It’s a stunning waterfall to say the least. Once you get to the one lane Concrete scooter paths take the left path all the way down until you get to the river and then park and walk on the path towards the falls. Do not ride down the concrete path if you are not very very confident with your scooter skills. It’s dangerous and steep. You can park and walk down if you chose
